Cabinet ministers will be deployed to the Western Cape to help in the fight against COVID-19. But it seems Premier Alan Winde has not been given details about this deployment. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Cabinet ministers will be deployed to the Western Cape to help in the fight against COVID-19. The province's Premier, Alan Winde, is questioning if this is more political than medical intervention. READ: Ramaphosa offers condolences to COVID-19 victims "I've tried to make sure politics does not get in the way of us trying to fight this virus. If people are asked to come and help - let's engage on how we can help each other get through this virus and let's not play politics," Winde said. Winde wants clarity from the national government on how the deployment will work. READ: COVID-19: SA death toll at 1080 The national COVID-19 death toll is at 1,080. South Africa's total number of confirmed cases is now at 50,879. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.